For example, at {{ill|Yasaka Shrine|ja|八坂神社}}, {{ill|Susanoo|ja|素戔嗚尊}} is enshrined as the main deity, with his consort {{ill|Kushinadahime|ja|櫛稲田姫命}} to the east and their "{{ill|Hachiōji Gongen|ja|八王子権現|Note=I’m not sure the proper translation. But it is not Eight pillar mikogami, that is an error based on the counter for gods|Lt=|lt=Eight mikogami}}" to the west. At {{ill|Kasuga Taisha|ja|春日大社|1=Kasuga-taisha}}, the auxiliary shrine "{{ill|Wakamiya Shrine|ja|若宮社}}" enshrines {{ill|Ame-no-Oshikumone|ja|天押雲根命}}, the Mikogami of the main deity {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|ja|天児屋根命}}.
